{
    "name": "Dire Bear (Cave Bear)",
    "type": "monster",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Ecology",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "<b>Environment</b> cold forests<br/><b>Organization</b> solitary or pair<br/><b>Treasure</b> incidental"
        },
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "Larger, more aggressive, and far more deadly than its lesser cousins, the dire bear (known to barbarian tribes variously as the cave bear or the short-faced bear) is a primeval menace indeed. This behemoth avoids more civilized reaches of the world, preferring to dwell in remote wilderness locations. A dire bear is a rare and terrifying sight\u2014especially to those not used to normal bears.<br/><br/>Unlike most bears, a dire bear is short-tempered and swift to anger when confronted with intruders in its territory. Like a grizzly, a dire bear attempts to subdue or kill with its claws. However, a dire bear is far more likely (and willing) to begin biting a grabbed foe."
        }
    ],
    "html": "<i>Spittle drips from this feral bear\u2019s roaring maw, and its matted fur is broken in places by wicked, bony growths.</i>",
